Black is beautiful & all the pain, hatred, racism etc. that we've endured helped to create the beautiful genre/culture known as Hip-Hop. We weren't hateful or selfish, as we've allowed all to take part in it! This should be celebrated! Love yall! Oh and... Rap Should Be Fun!!!!

I'll end by saying that while it would've been easy for me to yell and scream at this young, misguided man, he may have never opened his heart to see the Black perspective at all. I thank God for giving me the patience and for the ability to articulate something so important.

I was told that I had great patience and I feel that it was ALL God (cuz I've been known to see red during these types of talks lol) I feel that progress was made and things were learned. I believe it all happened as it was planned to.

I spent the next 45 minutes on a live with @hulveyofficial & the artist during which I truly felt God was present & working to help not only open the heart of this artist, but everyone who was present in the live.

I was fully able to articulate my points, give him a perspective he hadn't heard much in his life (a Black one) and get him to at least somewhat see where he was in the wrong. Later on, @hulveyofficial joined the live. Hulvey had been tagged in the artist's initial video.

After a pretty long back and forth that felt like it was going nowhere, he decided he was going to go live and clear up some things. He asked if I'd get on and I REALLY did NOT want to get on... but I'm glad I did. Once I joined I felt as if God had planned for me to do so.

This quote seemed to bother him greatly... 
“Blackness never needed Christian rap, but Christian rap is unimaginable without Blackness.” 

After finding out he had been following me, I decided to Dm him & try to speak to him civilly instead of saying what I initially wanted to.
